      COMPUTE/CONSOLIDATE‌‌

      ONESOURCE Income Tax offers several different methods for system computation. The TAS navigation tree changes depending on whether you are in a single entity or computing for a consolidation.

      COMPUTE. For a single binder, Compute displays on the TAS menu. On this screen, you can select the compute options and Working Trial Balance options to update Organizer with your Federal Tax Accounting System, State A&A or ONESOURCE State Apportionment, State TI TAS, Transfer International, and transfer Form 8865 K-1 data.

      CONSOLIDATE. For a consolidation, Consolidate displays on the TAS menu. This offers you the ability to run all underlying consolidations and computes from the Top Consolidation binder as well as run TAS consolidations and Organizer consolidations simultaneously.

      If you select any of these options, when you click Compute, the system will compute your Tax Accounting System data, transfer the balances to Organizer, and compute the tax return.

      If you do not have any of these options selected, when you click the Compute button, the system will compute only the Tax Accounting System data.


      The other method is the Auto Compute option within Organizer. This is a system option you can toggle on or off from the Options menu in Organizer. When the Auto Compute option is on, the system automatically computes the data in the tax return whenever you enter or change amounts. When the Auto Compute option is off, if you enter or change amounts, if you want to compute the tax return, you must click Full Recompute located on the File menu.

      When you select Full Recompute from the File menu, only the tax return will be computed. The balances from the Tax Accounting system will not re-transfer, and the Tax Accounting System will not compute.

      Computing or Consolidating in TAS

      1. On the TAS navigation tree, select Compute (for a consolidation binder select Consolidate). Make selections on each tab as applicable:

        Domestic Compute tab - Compute data in the Tax Accounting System and Tax Return based on each item selected:

        • Refresh Entity: "Company Information" and "Fiscal Year and Incorporation"

        • Refresh historical balances from prior year related binder

        • Update Organizer with Federal TAS

        • Update Organizer with State A&A or Update Organizer with ONESOURCE State Apportionment

        • Update Organizer with State TI TAS

        • Transfer 8865 K-1

        • Transfer International.

      2. Options tab - Select the applicable options that apply. Refer to “Options” on page 215.

         We do not recommend changing closing and rounding options at the binder level.

      3. Click Compute.

      This computes all of the data, beginning with data in the Tax Accounting System and continuing through the Organizer and Tax Return.

       If Update Organizer with Federal TAS , Update Organizer with State A&A, or Update Organizer with State TI TAS is selected, the system computes the Tax Accounting System data, transfers the balances to Organizer, and computes the tax return. If neither are selected, only the Tax Accounting System data computes.


      If you have changed any of the entity properties in the active entity, select the Refresh Entity: "Company Information" and "Fiscal Year and Incorporation" to pickup checkbox the changes.


      When you are in the Organizer section of the binder, the Auto Compute and Full Recompute options only compute the data in the Organizer and Tax Return.

      Consolidation Compute

      This screen processes Income Tax Returns consolidations and runs all underlying consolidations and computes from the Top Consolidation binder. This feature gives you the ability to:

    • Consolidate Federal, State A&A, State TI and Organizer simultaneously

    • Process consolidations and underlying members

    • Member binders are automatically listed on the Organizer, What to Consolidate screen.

      When you update member binders in the binder's Properties, the Consolidate screen then provides a list of all member binders including lower level consolidations and their members. This screen shows you the following information about the consolidation and each of its members:

    • Company Number (at the beginning in brackets)

    • Entity Name/Binder Name

    • Consol Options column

    • Needs Compute indicator

    • Last TAS Compute

    • Status column.

      ONESOURCE Income Tax 2016



      The ONESOURCE entity type icon appears next to each different entity to give you a hierarchal representation of your consolidation structure.


      BEST PRACTICES

      Use the Enterprise Control Panel to select options that apply to each of the consolidated binders before processing them, such as:

    • Detail Print Options - Use this area to select the Cross-tie or stacked print option and any other consolidated print option for each consolidated return binders.

    • States to Consolidate/Combine - Use this area to select the states in Organizer that will file combined or consolidated returns.

    • State Combined Options - Use this area to select combined options by state that need to be selected. For example, the Kansas combined income filing method.

    • What to Consolidate - Use this area to select Federal, State A&A, State TI, and Organizer as the data that needs to be consolidated for each consolidation binder. For example, set these options in Divisional or Sub consolidations before processing the Top Consolidation.

      Using the Consolidation Compute

      1. Open a Top Consolidation Tax Return binder.

      2. On the TAS navigation tree, select Consolidate.

      3. The Consolidation screen lists all the member binders for the consolidation.


        If there is a green marker in the Consol Options field , click the icon to access the Consolida- tion Options screen.

        The Consolidation screen is set up in spreadsheet format with the following columns. The columns give you information about the consolidation members and are described as follows:

        [Company Number] Entity/Binder

        This column shows the ONESOURCE entity type icon next to each different entity to give you a hierarchal representation of the consolidation structure.

        Consol Options

        This column shows the consolidation binders where you must select consolidation options which tell the soft- ware how to process the consolidation binder. Check the box(es) for the data you want to consolidate and the appropriate update option(s):

        Update Organizer with:

        • Federal TAS. Select this option to update this consolidation's Organizer with information from Federal TAS. This option is available for "Foreign entity" Divisional Consolidations or consolidations using the Binder Rollup option.

        • State A&A. Select this option to update this consolidation's Organizer with information from State Allocation and Apportionment. This option is available for Divisional Consolidations.

        • State TI. Select this option to update this consolidation's Organizer with information from the State TI data entry area. This option is available for Divisional Consolidations.

          Update International Organizer with Federal TAS (2004 and prior). Select this option to update Interna- tional Organizer with Federal TAS information. This option is only available for binders preceding 2005.

          Transfer International. Select this option to transfer international information to Foreign Tax Credit Divi- sional Consolidations.

          What to Consolidate


        • Federal - Select this to consolidate all Federal TAS information. This consolidates the Working Trial Balance, Schedule M-3, and all federal reports.

        • State A&A - Select this to consolidate State A&A data entry and review workpapers. You do not need this option for a federal consolidation.

        • State TI [requires state selection] - Select this to consolidate State TI data entry and review workpapers. In addition to selecting this, you must also select each state to consolidate State TI and activate each applicable state in Organizer in order to synchronize the State Tax Forms with the State TI review workpapers.


          If you select a state where you have manually entered amounts in the State TI data entry workpapers then these amounts will be overwritten with the consolidated amounts on the consolidated binder.

        • Organizer - Select this to consolidate the Organizer and Tax Forms and generate necessary information for filing the return.

        • Save Options - Click this button to save all of your choices for future processing sessions for this consolidation. Member binders, including underlying consolidations, should already have the same selections before processing the consolidation.

        • Close - Click this button to return to the Consolidation screen and continue the process. Needs Compute

          This column indicates whether or not there have been changes to this binder such as TAS data, binder prop- erty selections, related binder, or chart information. TAS data changes can include balances, adjustment balances, and Schedule M-3 data for tax return binders.

        • A Yes indicates the binder must be computed to reflect the changes.

        • A No indicates a compute is not needed for that member binder.

          Text Color

        • If a member binder needs to be computed, the text will be "blue" .

        • If it does not need a compute, then the text will be "black".

        • As member binders are processed, the text color will change to "green" indicating a member is being processed.

        • The text color "gray" indicates the binder is Read-Only. Last TAS Compute

        This column indicates the most recent date and time when the binder was successfully computed. Status

        This column represents the processing status of this consolidation binder and its members. Some of the sta- tus' include: Ready, TAS Computing, Opening Tax Data File, Tax Consolidating, Computing, Compute Never Finished, etc.).

        This column is important, especially when the consolidation process is unsuccessful. If the status is Com- pute Never Finished for a binder, you must process it again before continuing with the consolidation pro- cess.

      4. Before starting the consolidation process, select from the following options:

        • Compute and Consolidate Underlying Members. Select this option when you are ready to compute and consolidate members of this consolidation. Any binders set as "Read Only" will not compute. If you only want to process this consolidation and not underlying consolidations, do not select this option.

        • Only Consolidations. Select this option to compute and consolidate only consolidation members. When you select this option, all underlying consolidations will be processed and any other member binders will not be computed.

        • All Members. Select this option to compute and consolidate all members. When you select this option, any non-consolidated binders will also be computed. The compute of each member binder will use its own Update Federal TAS, State A&A, State TI, and Transfer International settings during the compute.

          ONESOURCE Income Tax 2016



        • Include Partnerships that use K-1 or A&A transfer. Select this option to compute and consolidate all partnership binders with corporate partners that are a part of this consolidation. These are the partnerships that flow to some members of this consolidation and they use the K-1 or A&A transfer feature.

        • Include Foreign and Foreign Partnership. Select this option to compute and consolidate all foreign entity binders and foreign partnerships that are International members in this consolidation. International computes are not included with this process.

        • Only If They Need Computing. Select this option to compute and consolidate only binders where the data has been changed but the computed results do not reflect the changes. The Needs Compute column shows the binders that would benefit from this option. Please contact your account manager if you would like to use this feature.

      5. Refresh history for this consolidation and underlying consolidations. Select this option to update each consolidation's historical balances from the prior year related binders.

      6. Click Begin to start the compute and consolidation processing. This button will not become active until you select the Consol Options. You must select them before beginning the process. After starting the consolidation, you can either leave this screen open or close it while the software processes the information.

      7. While the process is running, the Status column will show various status messages for each member and consolidation binder being processed.

      8. When the consolidation processes are complete, the Status column will show Ready in it.

      9. Click Export to export the consolidation member list into a .csv file. Locator numbers will appear next to each member.

      10. Click Close to close this screen after processing or without processing the consolidation.


      OPTIONS‌‌

      You can set TAS options several places in the system.

    • Federal Chart of Accounts

    • Binder Properties

    • Compute or Consolidate on the TAS tree

    • Enterprise Control Panel (if you have administrator rights.) The following options must be set for all binders using TAS.

    • Close Books to Retained Earnings Account

    • Post Rounding Difference to Balance Sheet Account

    • Round up to the Amount of

    • Post Translation Gain/Loss to Balance Sheet Account (if applicable)

    • State A&A Logic to be Applied

       The advantage to setting the options at the federal chart level is that any entity that you create based on the chart will default to the federal chart options.


      If you make changes to options at the federal chart level, you must update previously created entities and binders to reflect the change. New binders based on the chart automatically reflect the changes.


      If you change the options set at the entity level, you must update currently existing binders to reflect the changes.


      State A&A Logic to Apply (Consolidation Binders Only)

      If Consolidate Only is selected, the computed amounts from each member roll up into the Consolidation binder. These computed amounts display on the individual states' workpapers in the consolidated binder. Using Consolidate Only allows a different logic chart to be assigned to each member of the consolidation.

      If an actual logic chart is selected, the data entry amounts from each member will roll up into the Consolidation binder. The logic will then be applied to the rolled up data entry amounts in the Consolidation binder.

      State Logic charts are used to assign logic to the State categories and subcategories. Logic charts allow you to control how your data is summarized on a state-by-state basis. They allow you to designate whether a category/ subcategory is used for Income Tax and/or Franchise Tax apportionment.


      CURRENCY TRANSLATION‌‌

      Currency Translation is the last item on the TAS navigation menu. Use this screen to:

    • Assign the Exchange Rate Chart and select the local and functional currencies.

    • View the Exchange Rate Chart values.

    • Override the Exchange Rate Chart values.

    • Set Translation Options for both Local Currency to Functional Currency and Functional Currency to Local Currency.

    • Review and select other currency translation options. The Currency Translation screen has two tabs:

    • Local Currency to Functional Currency

    • Functional Currency to US Currency.


ONESOURCE Income Tax 2016



Selecting Currency Translation Options

  1. On the TAS navigation tree, click Currency Translation.

  2. Select the Exchange Rate Chart Assigned from the drop-down list.

  3. Select the Functional Currency from the drop-down list.

  4. On the Local Currency to Functional Currency screen, select the Local Currency from the drop-down list.

  5. Select Use Override Values to make entries that override the chart ratios, if desired.

  6. Select Rates By Account to enter rates for each of the individual accounts. If entries are made for individual accounts, then the system currency translation uses these account rates rather than the chart or chart override rates.

  7. Select the applicable Translation Option for each binder from the following:

    • Translate on an account by account basis. If exchange rate for an account is left blank, no translation will be done for that account.

    • Translate on an account by account basis. Weighted average rate is the default rate for accounts without a rate.

    • Translate on an account by account basis. (The system defaults to this option.) Weighted average rate is the default rate for the Income Statement accounts without a rate. Ending rate is the default rate for the Balance Sheet accounts without a rate.

  8. Select Functional Currency to US Currency.

  9. Review the current selections and make the appropriate changes.


ACTIVITY TRANSFER‌‌

For Form 8825 and Schedule K lines 2 and 3, the Activity Transfer feature gives you the ability to enter Rental Real Estate Income and Other Rental Income financial information into the tax accounting system. The application then transfers the data to the Organizer to generate Form 8825 in 1065, 1120S, and 1120 REIT returns.


SETTING UP ACTIVITY TRANSFER

Balances

TRC categories 38 and 48 are dedicated for Activity Transfer. The transfer from TAS to the Organizer is accomplished by assigning Activity Numbers and Activity Names. We added extra columns on the TAS Balances screen to accommodate this information.


Activity Information

The Activity Number and Activity Name list is unique for each return. You can only enter the information for accounts associated with TRC categories 38 and 48.

 For a list of Activity TRCs, refer to the TRC User Guide on Product Assistance.


The Activity Number can only use numbers from 1 through 999 and the Activity Name cannot be longer than 50 characters.

 If Form 8825 detail already exists in the Organizer, you must use the same Activity numbers when entering detail in TAS. The transfer process matches the Activity numbers and inserts the related TAS data. If the number does not match, the software will add a new activity in the Organizer.



ENTERING ACTIVITY INFORMATION

  1. Open a binder and access the Balances screen.

  2. Go to an Activity Number cell and right-click to see a list of Activity Numbers and Activity Names.


  3. Select the activity 000 – (New Activity Number).

  4. Click Submit to add a new activity. The Activity Number must be unique for each activity. Once you add a number, to remove it, you must delete it.

  5. To modify the Activity Name, select the activity and click Edit.

  6. Click OK to save all changes.

 You can also import Activity number(s) and Activity Name(s) into TAS Balances when you import the balance amounts.

ONESOURCE Income Tax 2016



TRANSFERRING ACTIVITY INFORMATION TO ORGANIZER

  1. On the TAS navigation tree, select Compute.

  2. Select the option Update Organizer with Federal TAS.

  3. Click the Compute button.



 If depreciation asset detail is imported using a DIF process prior to transferring data from TAS, you must compute the Organizer first so that the Organizer index is populated properly. Failure to do this can cause activities to be duplicated in the Organizer.


CHAPTER 11: ORGANIZER AND TAX FORMS‌‌


Organizer is the central collection point for all data in a given tax year. It is initially populated with balances, adjustments, and calculated amounts which flow from the Tax Accounting System (TAS). It also includes supporting schedules and return data that completes the tax return.


WEB ORGANIZER‌

For 1065 and 1120, you experience changes that have been made to update the screens for a more stan- dardized and modern look and feel, but the navigation, screen locations, and data entry are all the same.

DIFFERENCES BETWEEN WEB ORGANIZER AND CLASSIC ORGANIZER

After you delete a navigation node item, you will see a blank screen on the right.

When you right-click and select Related Items, the Web Organizer shows only actionable items. The Clas- sic Organizer showed items even if you could not navigate to the landing page.

You have the option to send feedback. Go to the Help menu and select the feedback option to send an email with specific screen information from the server. This will help us better understand your feedback.

You only need to single-click to open a folder on the navigation tree. Double-clicking is no longer neces- sary.


OPENING ORGANIZER TO WEB (OTW)

In a binder, on the TAS navigation menu, select Tax Return | Organizer.


ONESOURCE 2016



ORGANIZER TO WEB NAVIGATION

The Organizer toolbar provides easy navigation and basic commands.


Organizer to Web, or OTW, is available for 1120 and 1065 returns created for tax year 2016. Immediately you will notice the updated interface, which is cleaner and easier to navigate.

  1. The Tax Year, Tax Type, and Entity Name are prominently displayed at the top of the screen.

  2. The Organizer toolbar has been streamlined and drop-downs have been incorporated into the toolbar selections.

  3. The Organizer and Tax Forms tabs have been updated, and the Collapse All functionality has been moved out of the toolbar and is now easily accessible next to the Tax Forms tab.

  4. The tree structure within Organizer now has a new look and double-clicks are no longer required to access a screen. A single click will expand a folder or open a selected screen.

  5. The tabs within the Organizer screens are consistent with the new look and selected tabs are now easily identifiable by the orange font color.

Help

COMPUTE

There are two types of compute in Organizer, Auto Compute and Full Recompute.

Auto Compute

Auto Compute calculates Organizer data as it is entered. This allows the application to populate related Organizer fields as well as tax forms and schedules. Disabling Auto Compute can speed up some data entry in Organizer.

Click the Compute drop-down list to enable Auto. When you enable Auto Compute, the arrows to the left of

Compute on the toolbar will be orange. If Auto Compute is disabled, the arrows will be gray.


Full Recompute

A Full Recompute will calculate all Organizer data. Perform this for each member binder before consolidating. To perform a Full Recompute, click Compute drop-down and select Full Recompute.


DIAGNOSTICS

Diagnostics are available to determine inconsistencies, omissions, or errors. To access, select View | Diagnostics.


There are several categories of diagnostics triggered by an Organizer Compute: Severe, Informational, E-file Alerts, and E-File Rejects. E-file Validation Errors are NOT triggered by an Organizer Compute—they are triggered by a separate process (Federal E-file | Error Checking | General Validation File). Severe and informational diagnostics have no impact on your ability to E-file.

ONESOURCE 2016



PRINT

  1. On the Organizer toolbar, select Print to begin the print process.

  2. The Print Selection screen opens in a new window. On this screen you can:

    • Verify the return type to print

    • Select desired copy types

    • Include e-File attachments

    • Select the all returns, or portions of the return to print

    • Enter a file name

    • Create the print file

    • Review previous print history for the return

  3. To create a print file, select the file you wish to print.



  4. Enter a file name.

  5. Click Create.

     You can only print one selection at a time.

  6. On the Organizer toolbar, click History to see the status of the print process.

  7. Within History, you will see the file name that you entered, the print status, your print selection, start date and time, and end date and time.



  8. Once the print process has completed, there will be three available options in the Actions column: Open, Download, and Delete. Click Open to open the print file in PDF format within a separate browser window. Click Download to save the PDF to a desired location. Click Delete to delete the print file.


ORGANIZER SCREENS‌

When you open Organizer, you will see two tabs Organizer and Tax Forms. These tabs are designed for easy navigation using a tree-type navigation. To access screens, select a menu item in the navigation tree in the left pane of the screen, also called the Forms List Window. The related data entry screen or form displays in the right pane of the screen or the Forms Window.


QUICK TRACK

Quick Track is a navigation tool that allows easy navigation to the most frequently used Organizer screens.



Quick Track contains quick links to items in General Information, e-File, Pages 1-5, Schedule D, Form 4797, and Common State.

NAVIGATING FOLDERS - ORGANIZER DATA ENTRY

Organizer provides data entry fields to supplement data flowing from TAS. Amounts associated with TRCs are populated from TAS and transfer to Organizer.

 Entered amounts in TRC Organizer fields are automatically replaced with TAS data when performing a Full Recompute.


GENERAL INFORMATION

The General Information folder contains several data entry screens Entity Information, Return Information, Jurisdictional Locking, and Return/Entity Type Conversion. Use these screens to make selections and customize return and schedule options.



Much of the information in the General Information folder is automatically populated from the information entered in the Properties for the entity and binder. We recommend that you verify this information within Organizer:

 Using the F1 key while on a field in Organizer, opens specific help information related to that field.

Jurisdictional Locking

The Jurisdictional Locking tab displays the jurisdictions which have been locked to prevent further data entry or calculations in the return.


Return Entity Type



Use Entity Type and Return Information screens to select or change the return type and entity type for the return. These settings are applied automatically based on the binder’s properties which were selected when the binder was created. They can be changed later in the Organizer.

  1. Select the correct return type from the following:

    • 1120 - U.S. Corporation

    • 1120S - S Corporation

    • 1120F - Foreign Corporation

    • 1120-H - Homeowners Association

    • 1120-RIC - Regulated Investment Company

    • 1120-REIT - Real Estate Investment Trust

    • 1120-C - Cooperative Associations

  2. Select the entity type for the return:

    • corporate single entity

    • parent

    • subsidiary

    • division

    • eliminations company

    • top consolidation

    • subconsolidation.

      ONESOURCE 2016



      An entity type must be selected for calculations to work properly.

  3. If you select a return type and then wish to change it to a different return type, you must delete the calculations that were performed using the previous return type. To do this, check the delete box next to the old return type in the Change Return Type section, compute the return, then uncheck the delete box.
